parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Crank Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can be a safety hazard, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Loss of acceleration
strange noise from the engine compartment
oil pressure problem reading
engine shutdown.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Axle Rod Detachment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can be a safety hazard, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Abnormal rattling sound
smoke coming from under the hood
oil leaking from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Unknown Causes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can be a safety hazard, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Inability to accelerate or maintain speed
engine shutdown.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Causing Vehicle to Lock into Neutral or Park
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to suddenly lock into neutral or park while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle locks into neutral or park while driving
the vehicle stalls or stops running
the dashboard indicators flicker or go blank
the emergency brake locks
and the passenger door may not open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine vibrating and stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine vibrates
the vehicle stalls or stops running
the passenger compartment fills with smoke
the dashboard indicators go haywire
and the valve lifter may crack.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Causing Dashboard Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the dashboard indicators to malfunction, leading to a loss of critical information and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard indicators flicker or go blank
the ignition wiring is faulty
and the electric module may burn out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessively bright tail lights can cause glare and discomfort to other drivers, potentially leading to accidents or distractions on the road.
symptoms: The tail lights are intensely bright
causing glare or discomfort to other drivers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to slow down or stop abruptly, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions or other accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes lock up or slow down suddenly without any apparent reason
the vehicle skids or stops abruptly
no warning lights or indications of malfunction are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Supercruise system can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose control, leading to potential accidents or collisions, especially when the system fails to recognize the driver's input and attempts to regain control.
symptoms: The Supercruise system fails to turn off or disengage
the vehicle slows down or turns on the flashers
the system announces "Take Control of the Vehicle" despite the driver's attempts to regain control
the vehicle fights the driver's input and does not allow acceleration to keep up with traffic.
